results.title: "...As Dreams are Made on...", Part 3 of 3: Wake Up Call
Out Of The Blue (Into The Fire) [Part 1 of 3]
results.description: At the end of Silver Surfer Vol. 1 #18, the Surfer was poised to go on a rampage against mankind, but never did.  Why not?  And what did the Psycho-Man have to do with it? [per next issue box]

results.title: Broken! [Part 2 of 3]
results.description: What chance does Spider-Man have against a seriously cheesed off Silver Surfer?  Even worse, even if he does survive this onslaught of the power cosmic, can he really hope to stand up against Psycho-Man?  [per next issue box]

results.title: With Everything To Lose [Part 3 of 3]
results.description: Not only have Spidey and the Silver Surfer been transported to Sub-Atomica, not only do they have to contend with the machinations of Psycho-Man, but now Annihilus has joined the fray. [per next issue box]

results.title: The Bridge, Part 1 of 3
results.description: It's back to high school daze, as the talented team of Joe Kelly and Bart Sears revisit Peter Parker's senior prom!  As if ordinary prom night tensions weren't enough to give Pete an ulcer, who should crash the bash but none other than...the Sandman! [per next issue box]

results.title: The Bridge, Part 2 of 3
results.description: Peter Parker is finally at his senior prom, and could it be a worse time for a final showdown with his nemesis, Flash Thompson?  Well, yeah, if a mutated Sandman is on the loose!  Plus, who's Peter's date? [per next issue box]

results.title: The Bridge, Part 3 of 3
results.description: Who can honestly say their prom was broken up -- by the Sandman?!  Peter can, and now it's all his fault!  Now all he's got to do is halt Sandy's Coney Island rampage, salvage his college scholarship, and escort not one, not two, but three dates to the prom. [per next issue box]
